OL,3,CTrial offers glimmer of hope for
OL,4,Cpatients with incurable brain cancer
OL,6,FGlioblastoma is the most common
OL,7,Fprimary brain tumour in adults.
OL,9,FIt is estimated that about 3,200
OL,10,Fpeople in the UK are diagnosed with
OL,11,Fthe disease each year, surviving on
OL,12,Faverage for 12 to 18 months.
OL,14,FFive people with suspected high-grade
OL,15,Ftumours are currently enrolled on the
OL,16,Ftrial, which is being led by
OL,17,Fscientists from Queen Mary University
OL,18,Fof London and Barts Brain Tumour
OL,19,FCentre.
